  <!-- ── SERVICE CLARITY ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">What we do</p>
      <h2>We repair every JennAir dishwasher configuration.</h2>
      <p>Standard JDB built-in dishwashers (JDB1100, JDB1250, JDB2150, JDB3200, JDB3600, JDB4000, JDB6510, JDB8200, JDB8910 families). Professional-design JDPSS models with commercial-style handles. Fully-integrated panel-ready dishwashers for custom cabinet panel installation. Both RISE Collection (brushed stainless, commercial handles) and NOIR Collection (black stainless finishes, minimalist controls).</p>
      <p>We carry the common failure parts on every truck: drain pumps, water inlet valves, door latch assemblies, spray arms, check valves, thermistors. OWI sensors and control boards available within 24-48 hours through Whirlpool Corp parts network. For water filter replacements, we stock EDR4RXD1 cartridges.</p>
      <p>We're not JennAir-authorized (that network handles in-warranty dispatch — call 1-800-536-6247 for units under 1-year base warranty). We're post-warranty specialists: <strong>BHGS #A49573, BHGS #A49573, BBB A+ since 2022</strong>. Most of our JennAir dishwasher calls are 3-to-14-year-old units across Beverly Hills, Brentwood, Sherman Oaks, Studio City, Encino, Pasadena, and Calabasas on the LA side; Newport Coast, Newport Beach, and Tustin in OC; Westlake Village, Hidden Hills, and Thousand Oaks in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country in the IE.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── MODELS ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Models we service</p>
      <h2>JennAir dishwasher model families</h2>

      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JDB Current Generation</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDB9200 · JDB9800 · JDB9910 · JDB4000AWX · JDB6510AWP</p>
          <p>Current-generation built-in dishwashers with TriFecta wash system (three-stage filtration), OWI Optical Water Indicator (detects debris level and adjusts cycle), pro-style racking. Home Connect Wi-Fi on 2020+ models. Shared Whirlpool Corp platform with KitchenAid KDTE/KDTM counterparts — most service components cross-compatible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JDPSS Professional Design</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDPSS244BL · JDPSS244BX · JDPSS245BS</p>
          <p>Pro-style handle designs with commercial-grade aesthetic. Same internal architecture as JDB models — same circulation pump, drain pump, control boards. The differentiator is handle and finish styling, not functional engineering. RISE Collection commercial handles on stainless, or NOIR black stainless with minimalist trim.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JDB8910 / JDB8200 (Earlier High-End)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDB8910AWS · JDB8910AWB · JDB8910AWW · JDB8200AWS3</p>
          <p>Earlier JennAir premium dishwashers, 2010-2016. Known for premature-drain issue pattern on JDB8200 family (fills, then drains and powers off after ~1 minute) — usually door latch sensor or water inlet valve. Still serviceable, parts availability good through Whirlpool Corp network.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JDB1250 / JDB2150 (Mid-Range Legacy)</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDB1250AWP · JDB1250AWS · JDB2150AWP · JDB2100AWS</p>
          <p>Mid-range JennAir dishwashers, 2008-2014. Common issue on JDB2150AWP: door lock won't stay latched (small click but won't engage) — latch assembly replacement $185-$265. JDB1250 common issue: drain pump hardened deposit buildup blocking impeller (Southern California hard-water accelerated; worst in IE districts). Cleaning often sufficient before pump replacement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Fully-Integrated Panel-Ready</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDB-PR variants · JDPSS panel-ready · custom cabinet integration</p>
          <p>Panel-ready configurations where owner's custom cabinet panel attaches to dishwasher front for seamless kitchen integration (flush with surrounding cabinetry, no visible appliance). Common in luxury renovations across our service area — Brentwood, Pacific Palisades, and Hollywood Hills on the LA side; Newport Coast and Coto de Caza in OC; Westlake Village and Hidden Hills in Ventura; and Rancho Cucamonga and Temecula wine-country contemporary kitchens — where aesthetic continuity matters. Service difference: panel removal/reinstallation adds 20-30 min labor; panel weight varies by material ($85-$145 panel mounting hardware).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>JDB1080 / JDB1090 / JDB1100 Legacy</h3>
          <p class="model-list">JDB1080AWS · JDB1090AWS · JDB1100AWB · JDB1100AWS</p>
          <p>Legacy JennAir dishwashers 2005-2010. Still serviceable for common failures (drain pump, door gasket, spray arms). Some electronic parts have reduced availability on 15+ year units. Honest repair-vs-replace on pre-2010 — most mechanical repairs still make sense, electronic failures borderline.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── COMMON PROBLEMS ── -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Common failures</p>
      <h2>The eight things that break on a JennAir dishwasher</h2>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>1. Won't drain — drain pump or hardened deposits (#1 call across our service area)</h3>
        <p>Most common JennAir dishwasher call across our 8 service territories. Southern California hard water (200-350 ppm in LA / OC / Ventura, 300-450+ ppm in IE) accelerates mineral deposit formation on drain pump impeller, which gradually restricts water flow until pump hums but can't move water. Five-step diagnostic: (1) inspect sump/filter for food debris (40% of calls free fix), (2) check drain hose for kinks behind dishwasher, (3) inspect drain pump impeller — hardened deposits need cleaning or pump $165-$245, (4) drain hose check valve stuck closed $125-$175, (5) control board drain relay failure $485-$680. Prevention: monthly vinegar rinse cycle + filter cleaning reduces mineral buildup.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>2. Fills then drains and shuts off (JDB8200 pattern)</h3>
        <p>Specific pattern common on JDB8200AWS3 and similar models. Dishwasher fills normally, then after ~1 minute drains and powers off before wash phase begins. Diagnostic: door latch sensor failed (control doesn't see door as locked even though mechanically closed) $185-$265, OR water inlet valve malfunction (valve doesn't close properly, control aborts on abnormal pressure) $185-$265, OR backflow through check valve triggering OWI sensor $125-$175. We run diagnostic mode to identify which of the three before ordering parts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>3. Door latch / lock failure</h3>
        <p>Door won't stay latched — small click when closing but no engagement. Common on JDB2150AWP family specifically. Latch assembly wear over 8-12 years: mechanism loses spring tension, can't hold closed under internal pressure during wash cycle. Replacement $185-$265. On fully-integrated panel-ready models, latch replacement requires panel temporary removal adding 20 min labor. We verify with diagnostic mode door-lock test before ordering — rare but control board relay can mimic latch failure ($485-$680 board vs $215 latch).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>4. Stuck buttons / unresponsive panel</h3>
        <p>JennAir/KitchenAid/Maytag shared diagnostic procedure: unplug, disconnect user interface wire harness, restore power, wait 7 seconds for board initialization, close door. If drain pump briefly runs = UI control failed ($385-$545). If drain pump doesn't run = electronic control board failed ($485-$680). This one-test diagnostic saves ordering the wrong $500+ part — we run this every time before any panel-related parts recommendation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>5. Thermistor / OWI sensor failure</h3>
        <p>Thermistor monitors water temperature; OWI (Optical Water Indicator) detects debris level in rinse water and adjusts cycle length automatically. When thermistor drifts: wash cycles run too cold (poor cleaning) or too hot (energy waste). Thermistor $95-$145. When OWI fails: dishwasher runs longest cycle every time (doesn't detect "clean enough" to shorten) or conversely runs too-short cycles. OWI sensor $145-$215. Diagnostic mode shows current sensor readings so we verify drift before replacement.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>6. Circulation pump failure — no spray pressure</h3>
        <p>Circulation pump is the main wash motor driving water through spray arms. Failure symptoms: dishwasher runs through full cycle timing but items emerge dirty or barely wet, humming from pump area without water movement, sometimes F-code displayed on Home Connect models. Circulation pump assembly $345-$485, 90-min job. Usually failure at year 9-13 on heavy-use units. Shared Whirlpool Corp pump across JennAir/KitchenAid — parts availability good.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>7. Leaking — door seal or tub gasket</h3>
        <p>Water pooling on floor in front of dishwasher during or after cycles. Two primary causes. Door seal (runs around door perimeter) — wear, tear, or food debris impaction over 8-12 years $145-$215. Tub gasket (between door assembly and tub) — rarer failure but can occur on 10+ year units $125-$185. Third cause: inlet hose connection under dishwasher loose $85 flat re-seating. We inspect all three before parts recommendation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem">
        <h3>8. Spray arm blocked or damaged</h3>
        <p>Cleaning performance drops, specific rack positions cleaning poorly. Spray arm holes clogged with hard-water mineral deposits (a pattern across all of Southern California, particularly the IE) or food debris. Cleaning: remove spray arm, soak in vinegar 30 min, scrub with brush — free DIY or $85 flat during service visit. Damaged spray arm (cracked, broken, wobbly rotation): replacement $85-$145 per arm. Upper rack spray arm most commonly damaged by loaded rack catching on it during insertion. Two or three spray arms per dishwasher depending on model.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── LA HARD WATER INSIGHT ── -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow-sub">Southern California insight</p>
      <h2>Southern California hard water and JennAir dishwasher service economics</h2>
      <p>SoCal water hardness (200-350 ppm in most of LA / OC / Ventura, 300-450+ ppm in the Inland Empire — Rancho Cucamonga, Riverside, Temecula) accelerates specific JennAir dishwasher failure modes disproportionately compared to soft-water regions.</p>
      <p>Drain pump impeller hardening is the #1 SoCal-accelerated failure — mineral deposits accumulate on the impeller edges over 6-9 years across LA / OC / Ventura (and 4-6 years in the IE) versus 12-15 years in soft-water regions, restricting water flow until pump hums but can't drain. Spray arm hole clogging is #2 — hole openings narrow from deposit accumulation, reducing cleaning effectiveness progressively. Heating element scale buildup is #3 — thick mineral scale reduces heat transfer, extends cycle time, raises energy costs.</p>
      <p>Preventive routine specific to LA: monthly vinegar rinse cycle (fill dispenser with white vinegar, run empty hot cycle) dissolves accumulated mineral deposits before they harden. Quarterly filter cleaning ensures debris doesn't compact into sump area. Annual professional descaling service ($95 flat) removes scale from heating element and hidden surfaces. With this routine, LA JennAir dishwashers frequently reach 12-14 year service life despite hard water; without it, 8-10 years is more typical.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

